For the historical changes from 1979 to 2016 (Fig. 1a, b), we used the ERA-Interim reanalysis data
48 , which capture the historical SIC seasonal cycle and changes fairly realistically, although the mean SIC is somewhat lower than satellite observations from NOAA (Supplementary Figure 2). The ERA-Interim data have been used to study Arctic climate and SIC change in many previous studies;
3, 23, 28, 47 they arguably represent one of our best datasets available for the Arctic region.
